CompanyDescription.label: Company Description
CompanyDescription.value: Formed in 2004 by the combination of IMC Global and Cargill's fertilizer business, Mosaic is a leading producer of primary crop nutrients phosphate and potash. The company's assets include phosphate rock mines in Florida, Louisiana, Brazil and Peru and potash mines in Saskatchewan, New Mexico, and Brazil.
